  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">CROIX ROUGE DU BURUNDI</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Burundian Red Cross: the BRC is the only organization benefiting from a network of workers and volunteer at all decentralized levels: from the national level to the level of collines and sous-collines. The BRC is the only local organization with the capacity to intervene and provide urgent responses in nearly all sectors everywhere in Burundi and benefiting from the legitimacy (toward the GoBespecially) to provide urgent response to population#s need.

As the sole local humanitarian actor with this kind of capacities thered cross is over-solicitated for all type of responses. At local level when there is a shock it is first toward the BRC that headsturn for immediate intervention and capacities. Due to this and to the lack of humanitarian funding inBurundi the capacities of theBRC are stretched and there main challenge is the lack of financial and material means to implement a response.</narrative>
  </description>
  <participating-org role="4" type="24">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Croix Rouge du Burundi</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Burundi Red Cross (CRB) is a voluntary relief society duly recognized by all authorized national and international bodies. She works all over the national territory and takes care, among other things, of alleviating the suffering of people.
Its daily activities are carried out through the support programs and departments set up for this purpose.

The National Society&apos;s operational programs are:
Organizational development

Disaster management and assistance to the vulnerable

Health and Care

Communication-Diffusion ofhumanitarian standards.

Added to this is the Finance, Administration and Logistics Department

All Red Cross activities must respect the 7 Fundamental Principles of the International Red Cross and Red Crescent Movement, namely:
Humanity, Impartiality, Neutrality, Independence, Volunteering, Unity and Universality.</narrative>
  </participating-org>
